## Real code in this repo

- **Clickable links (required):** When referencing a file/line range, include a **markdown link** that opens in the editor in one click. Use the **`vscode://file/`** URI (VS Code / Cursor):
  - **Pattern:** `[label](vscode://file/<absolute-path-to-file>:<startLine>)`
  - **Path:** Absolute path to the file from the repo/workspace root, use **forward slashes** after the drive letter on Windows (e.g. `c:/Users/.../NoGravityWebsite/src/ui/screen-dials.js`).
  - **Encoding:** URL-encode spaces and special characters (`%20` for space).
  - **Line:** `:<startLine>` at the end jumps to the **first** line of the range (same as the old “start:end:path” first number).
  - **Example:** `[screen-dials — Bloom row](vscode://file/c:/Users/you/project/src/ui/screen-dials.js:17)`
- **Do not** rely on ` ```startLine:endLine:filepath` alone as the only navigation hint — it is often **not** clickable in chat; **links first**.
- **Optional:** After the link, a short backtick line for copy-paste: `` `src/ui/screen-dials.js` (lines 17–23) ``.
- **Syntax highlighting for real code (required):** When you paste **actual** source from this repo, put it in a fenced block with a **language id** so it renders **syntax-colored** in Cursor (same idea as pseudocode). Use **` ```javascript `** for `.js`, **` ```typescript `** for `.ts`/`.tsx`, **` ```css `**, **` ```html `**, **` ```json `**, **` ```shell `**, etc. Do **not** use a bare ` ``` ` or ` ```text ` for real code when a specific highlighter applies. If you only have a ` ```startLine:endLine:path ` citation block and it appears **un-colored**, add a **duplicate** snippet under **` ```javascript `** (or the right tag) with the same lines so the user gets **color + navigation** (link first, then colored block).
- **Showing code:** **Pseudocode** = spec with `// pseudocode`, wrapper In/Out if any, and **per-step `//` sentences with typed inputs/outputs** (no `methodName(args)` steps); **real code** = same file content with the **file’s** language tag. Both should be colored when possible.

